          "id": "dantrolene_rescue",
          "titleTr": "Dantrolen Hesaplayıcı"
        }
      ],
      "relatedDrugCards": [
        {
          "id": "ephedrine",
          "titleTr": "Efedrin Monografı"
        },
        {
          "id": "norepinephrine",
          "titleTr": "Noradrenalin Monografı"
        }
      ],
      "doNotMiss": [
        "CPR sırasında göğüs geri yayılımına izin vermek ve kompresyon kesintilerini minimum tutmak"
      ],
      "whenToEscalate": [
        "Spontan dolaşımın dönmesi (ROSC) sonrası post-arrest yoğun bakım yönetimine geçiş"
      ],
      "referencesToShow": [
        "AHA Guidelines for CPR and ECC. Circulation 2020. PMID: 33081529.",
        "ERC Guidelines for Resuscitation 2021. PMID: 33773824."
      ],
      "safetyLevel": "emergency"
    },
    "en": {
      "notASubstituteWarning": "🚨 PATIENT IN CARDIAC ARREST! INITIATE CARDIAC ARREST / ACLS RESUSCITATION PROTOCOL IMMEDIATELY!",
      "conversationalText": "1. Declare arrest and call for help.\\n2. Start high-quality CPR: 100–120 compressions/min, depth about 5–6 cm, minimal interruptions.\\n3. Give 100% oxygen and use capnography.\\n4. Analyze rhythm: defibrillate VF/pulseless VT; for PEA/asystole continue CPR and give epinephrine.\\n5. Actively search reversible causes: hypoxia, hypovolemia, hydrogen ion/acidosis, hypo/hyperkalemia, hypothermia; tamponade, tension pneumothorax, thrombosis, toxins.\\n6. Do not miss anesthesia-specific causes such as high spinal, anaphylaxis, LAST, MH, bleeding, or oxygen/ventilation failure.",
      "immediateRedFlags": [
        "No pulse, apnea, or ECG showing Asystole/VF/Pulseless VT/PEA.",
        "Critical cerebral and systemic hypoxia starts within seconds."
      ],
      "missingCriticalInformation": [
        "Current ECG rhythm (Shockable vs Non-shockable)",
        "Patient estimated weight for dosing"
      ],
      "likelyClinicalCategoriesToConsider": [
        "Cardiac Arrest (VF/VT/PEA/Asystoli)",
        "Reversible Causes (5Hs & 5Ts: Hypoxia, Hypovolemia, Acidosis, Hypo/Hyperkalemia, Hypothermia; Tamponade, Pneumothorax, Thrombosis, Toxins)"
      ],
      "suggestedNextStepsGeneral": [
        "Declare Code Blue and bring the defibrillator immediately.",
        "Start uninterrupted, high-quality chest compressions (100-120/min, 5-6 cm depth).",
        "If Shockable (VF/VT): Deliver 1 shock (200 J) and resume CPR.",
        "If Non-shockable (Asystole/PEA): Give Epinephrine 1 mg IV/IO immediately, repeat every 3-5 min."
      ],
