        "Coronary Stent Thrombosis Risk Evaluation",
        "Regional Anesthesia Alternatives (General Anesthesia, Peripheral Nerve Blocks)"
      ],
      "suggestedNextStepsGeneral": [
        "Hold Clopidogrel for at least 5-7 days before elective neuraxial blocks.",
        "In patients with coronary stents, always consult Cardiology before holding antiplatelet therapy.",
        "If the drug cannot be stopped safely, prefer general anesthesia or shallow peripheral blocks under ultrasound guidance."
      ],
