          "id": "ephedrine",
          "titleTr": "Efedrin Monografı"
        }
      ],
      "doNotMiss": [
        "LAST arrestinde standart resüsitasyondan farklı olarak Vasopressin verilmemeli ve Adrenalin dozu <1 mcg/kg (örn. 10-100 mcg) olarak sınırlandırılmalıdır"
      ],
      "whenToEscalate": [
        "Maksimum lipid dozuna (12 mL/kg) rağmen kardiyovasküler stabilite sağlanamazsa acil ECMO/CPB desteği"
      ],
      "referencesToShow": [
        "ASRA Checklist for Local Anesthetic Systemic Toxicity. 2020.",
        "Neal JM, et al. PMID: 29016373."
      ],
      "safetyLevel": "emergency"
    },
    "en": {
      "notASubstituteWarning": "This response does not replace clinical judgment. Base decisions on your clinical assessment.",
      "conversationalText": "For 20% lipid emulsion:\\nBolus: 1.5 mL/kg IV.\\nInfusion: 0.25 mL/kg/min.\\n\\nRepeat bolus and increase infusion if instability persists.\\nRespect the maximum total dose. The ASRA checklist recommends not exceeding 12 mL/kg total lipid dose. LAST resuscitation differs from standard ACLS; avoid high-dose epinephrine and vasopressin.",
      "immediateRedFlags": [
        "Standard ACLS guidelines must be modified in the event of LAST-induced asystole or ventricular fibrillation.",
        "Delaying lipid rescue therapy significantly increases the risk of irreversible cardiovascular collapse."
      ],
      "missingCriticalInformation": [
        "Patient's exact weight (for accurate volume calculation)",
        "Total amount and type of local anesthetic injected"
      ],
      "likelyClinicalCategoriesToConsider": [
        "20% Lipid Emulsion (Intralipid) Rescue Mechanism",
        "Modified ACLS Protocol in LAST Resuscitation",
        "Lipid Emulsion Cumulative Dosing Limits"
      ],
      "suggestedNextStepsGeneral": [
        "Ensure 100% O₂ and secure the airway immediately.",
        "20% Lipid Emulsion: Administer 1.5 mL/kg IV bolus (approx. 100 mL, over 1 min).",
        "Immediately start a continuous infusion at 0.25 mL/kg/min (approx. 15-20 mL/min).",
        "Continue infusion for at least 15 minutes after hemodynamic stability is restored."
      ],
      "relatedAlgorithms": [
        {
          "id": "coagulation_management",
          "titleTr": "Coagulation Management Algorithm"
        },
        {
          "id": "cico_crisis",
          "titleTr": "CICO Emergency Algorithm"
