          "titleTr": "Kalsiyum Glukonat Monografı"
        }
      ],
      "doNotMiss": [
        "AFE'nin klasik üçlemesini: ani hipoksi, derin hipotansiyon ve ani gelişen tüketim koagülopatisi (DIC)"
      ],
      "whenToEscalate": [
        "Maternal resüsitasyona yanıt alınamayan arrest olgusunda, arrestin 4. dakikasında perimortem sezaryeni (PMCD) geciktirmeden uygulayın"
      ],
      "referencesToShow": [
        "Society for Maternal-Fetal Medicine (SMFM) Special Report on AFE. AJOG 2016.",
        "APSF Clinical Advisory on Amniotic Fluid Embolism. 2020."
      ],
      "safetyLevel": "emergency"
    },
    "en": {
      "notASubstituteWarning": "This response does not replace clinical judgment. Base decisions on your clinical assessment.",
      "conversationalText": "Amniotic fluid embolism is rare but catastrophic. It may present with sudden hypoxemia, hypotension/cardiovascular collapse, seizure/altered consciousness, and rapidly developing coagulopathy. Management is supportive: high-quality resuscitation, 100% oxygen, early intubation/ventilation, vasopressors/inotropes, aggressive coagulopathy treatment, MTP, fibrinogen replacement, and obstetric bleeding control. In maternal arrest, perform left uterine displacement and consider perimortem cesarean when appropriate. Early recognition and goal-directed treatment are critical.",
      "immediateRedFlags": [
        "Sudden cardiovascular collapse, cyanosis, and cardiac arrest during labor or immediately postpartum.",
        "Abrupt onset of severe, diffuse surgical or mucosal bleeding (hyperacute DIC)."
      ],
      "missingCriticalInformation": [
        "Fetal delivery status and duration of maternal cardiac arrest",
        "Immediate access to point-of-care coagulation diagnostics (ROTEM/TEG)"
      ],
      "likelyClinicalCategoriesToConsider": [
        "Amniotic Fluid Embolism (AFE) Crisis Management",
        "Maternal Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation Protocols",
        "Obstetric Coagulopathy and DIC Management"
      ],
      "suggestedNextStepsGeneral": [
        "Declare a major obstetric crisis, call for help, and secure the airway with 100% oxygen immediately.",
        "Provide aggressive vasopressor and inotropic support (e.g. epinephrine, dobutamine) for right-heart failure.",
        "Activate the Massive Transfusion Protocol (MTP) early, prioritizing fibrinogen concentrate or cryoprecipitate.",
        "If cardiac arrest occurs, apply left uterine displacement and perform a perimortem cesarean delivery if no ROSC in 4 minutes."
      ],
      "relatedAlgorithms": [
        {
          "id": "amniotic_fluid_embolism",
          "titleTr": "AFE Management Algorithm"
        },
        {
          "id": "maternal_arrest",
          "titleTr": "Maternal Cardiac Arrest"
        },
        {
          "id": "massive_bleeding",
          "titleTr": "Massive Transfusion Protocol (MTP)"
        }
      ],
      "relatedCalculators": [
        {
          "id": "fibrinogen_dose",
          "titleTr": "Fibrinogen Deficit Calculator"
        },
        {
          "id": "map",
          "titleTr": "Mean Arterial Pressure"
        }
      ],
      "relatedDrugCards": [
        {
          "id": "norepinephrine",
          "titleTr": "Norepinephrine Monograph"
        },
        {
          "id": "epinephrine",
          "titleTr": "Epinephrine Monograph"
        },
        {
          "id": "tranexamic_acid",
          "titleTr": "Tranexamic Acid Monograph"
        },
        {
          "id": "calcium_gluconate",
          "titleTr": "Calcium Gluconate Monograph"
        }
      ],
      "doNotMiss": [
        "AFE typically presents with a classic triad: sudden hypoxia, profound hypotension, and consumptive coagulopathy (DIC)"
      ],
      "whenToEscalate": [
        "In maternal cardiac arrest, if spontaneous circulation is not restored within 4 minutes, execute perimortem cesarean delivery"
      ],
      "referencesToShow": [
        "Society for Maternal-Fetal Medicine (SMFM) Special Report on AFE. AJOG 2016.",
        "APSF Clinical Advisory on Amniotic Fluid Embolism. 2020."
      ],
      "safetyLevel": "emergency"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "jehovah_blood_refusal",
    "category": "clinical_scenarios",
    "keywords": [
