          "titleTr": "Ondansetron"
        }
      ],
      "doNotMiss": [
        "Profilaktik ilaçların midenin boşalmasını garantilemediğini, sadece aspire edilen içeriğin asiditesini azaltarak akciğer hasarını hafiflettiğini, bu nedenle mekanik havayolu korumasının (balonlu tüp) şart olduğunu"
      ],
      "whenToEscalate": [
        "Hasta aktif olarak kusuyorsa veya mekanik intestinal obstrüksiyonu varsa, uyanık nazogastrik dekompresyon yapın, sol lateral/baş yukarı pozisyonda indüksiyon planlayın ve deneyimli havayolu yöneticisi çağırın"
      ],
      "referencesToShow": [
        "2023 American Society of Anesthesiologists Practice Guidelines for Preoperative Fasting.",
        "Miller's Anesthesia, 9th Edition."
      ],
      "safetyLevel": "elective"
    },
    "en": {
      "notASubstituteWarning": "This response does not replace clinical judgment. Base decisions on your clinical assessment.",
      "conversationalText": "In high aspiration-risk patients, drugs alone do not guarantee safety; airway strategy is central. Medications may help reduce gastric volume/acidity or nausea. Options include nonparticulate antacid, H₂ blocker/PPI, metoclopramide, and antiemetic. However, in bowel obstruction, active vomiting, or full stomach, medications do not eliminate aspiration risk. Assess fasting status and risk factors, and prepare RSI/full-stomach approach, head-up position, strong suction, and experienced intubation. ([PubMed])",
      "immediateRedFlags": [
        "Active bowel obstruction (ileus), persistent vomiting, or severe gastroparesis.",
        "Altered mental status with inability to protect the airway.",
        "History of gastroesophageal reflux (GERD) with active, frequent regurgitation."
      ],
      "missingCriticalInformation": [
        "The patient's exact fasting time (hours for solids and clear liquids)",
        "Co-existing risk factors such as obesity, advanced pregnancy, or diabetic gastroparesis"
      ],
      "likelyClinicalCategoriesToConsider": [
        "Aspiration Prophylaxis",
        "Full Stomach Management",
        "Preoperative Fasting Guidelines"
      ],
      "suggestedNextStepsGeneral": [
        "For high-risk patients, administer a nonparticulate antacid (e.g., sodium citrate) 30-60 minutes before induction.",
        "Give an H2 blocker (e.g., famotidine) or PPI to raise gastric pH.",
        "Administer metoclopramide to accelerate gastric emptying (if not contraindicated).",
        "Utilize a strict Rapid Sequence Induction (RSI) protocol for airway management."
      ],
      "relatedAlgorithms": [
        {
          "id": "aspiration_risk",
          "titleTr": "Aspiration Risk"
        },
        {
