    "en": {
      "safetyLevel": "routine",
      "notASubstituteWarning": "This response does not replace clinical judgment.",
      "conversationalText": "💉 Initial steps include rapid fluid co-loading and immediate administration of vasopressors. Use Phenylephrine (50-100 mcg IV bolus) if heart rate is normal/elevated; use Ephedrine (5-10 mg IV bolus) if bradycardia is present. Position the patient with left lateral tilt in obstetrics.",
      "immediateRedFlags": [],
