      "hypotension",
      "post",
      "spinal",
      "var0"
    ],
    "question_tr": "Spinal hipotansiyon tedavisinin komplikasyonları nelerdir?",
    "question_en": "What are the complications of spinal hypotension treatment?",
    "safetyLevel": "routine",
    "tr": {
      "safetyLevel": "routine",
      "notASubstituteWarning": "Bu asistan bir hekimin klinik kararı yerine geçemez.",
      "conversationalText": "🚨 Hatalı dozlama sonucu reaktif hipertansif kriz, sol ventrikül yüklenmesi, akciğer ödemi ve aritmiler gelişebilir. Aşırı fenilefrin uteroplasental perfüzyonu bozabilir (reaktif bradikardiyle). Efedrin ise fötal asidoz riskini fenilefrine göre artırır.",
      "immediateRedFlags": [],
      "missingCriticalInformation": [],
      "likelyClinicalCategoriesToConsider": [
        "Klinik Gerekçe",
        "Takip Yönetimi"
      ],
      "suggestedNextStepsGeneral": [],
      "relatedAlgorithms": [],
      "relatedCalculators": [],
      "relatedDrugCards": [],
      "doNotMiss": [],
      "whenToEscalate": [],
      "referencesToShow": []
    },
    "en": {
      "safetyLevel": "routine",
      "notASubstituteWarning": "This response does not replace clinical judgment.",
      "conversationalText": "🚨 Overtreatment can cause reactive hypertensive crisis, acute left ventricular strain, pulmonary congestion, and arrhythmias. Excessive Phenylephrine can impair uteroplacental perfusion via bradycardia. Ephedrine carries a higher risk of fetal acidosis than Phenylephrine.",
      "immediateRedFlags": [],
      "missingCriticalInformation": [],
      "likelyClinicalCategoriesToConsider": [
        "Clinical Rationale",
        "Follow-up Management"
