      "notASubstituteWarning": "This response does not replace clinical judgment.",
      "conversationalText": "🔄 Superficial peripheral nerve blocks where compression can be easily applied (e.g. Femoral, Saphenous, or Axillary blocks) carry negligible spinal hematoma risk and are much safer alternatives to neuraxial blockade. General anesthesia remains the standard fallback.",
